{"article_id":"ZhUhOzXs5WzcwNsV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The truth about how you can catch coronavirus ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"who is most vulnerable","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"and what you can do","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"to avoid infection","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Wearing a face mask is certainly not an iron-clad guarantee","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"that you won ' t get sick","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"-","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"viruses can also transmit through the eyes","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"and tiny viral particles ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"known as aerosols ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"can penetrate masks .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"However , masks are effective at capturing droplets ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"which is a main transmission route of coronavirus ,","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"and some studies have estimated a roughly fivefold protection versus no barrier alone","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"( although others have found lower levels of effectiveness ) .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"If you are likely to be in close contact with someone infected ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"a mask cuts the chance","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"of the disease being passed on .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"If you ' re showing symptoms of coronavirus ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"or have been diagnosed ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"wearing a mask can also protect others .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"So masks are crucial for health and social care workers","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"looking after patients","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"and are also recommended for family members","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"who need to care for someone","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"who is ill -","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"ideally both the patient and carer should have a mask .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"However , masks will probably make little difference","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"if you ' re just walking around town or taking a bus","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"so there is no need to bulk-buy a huge supply .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"All viruses accumulate mutations over time","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"and the virus","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"that causes Covid-19","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"is no different .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"How widespread different strains of a virus become depends on natural selection -","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"the versions","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"that can propagate quickest","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"and replicate effectively in the body","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"will be the most \" successful \" .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"This doesn ' t necessarily mean most dangerous for people though ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"as viruses","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"that kill people rapidly","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"or make them so sick","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"that they are incapacitated","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"may be less likely to be transmitted .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Genetic analysis by Chinese scientists of 103 samples of the virus ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"taken from patients in Wuhan and other cities ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"suggests","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that early on two main strains emerged ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"designated L and S.","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Although the L strain appeared to be more prevalent than the S strain","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"( about 70 % of the samples belonged to the former ) ,","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"the S branch of the virus was found to be the ancestral version .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"The team behind this research suggested","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"that this may indicate","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"the L strain is more \" aggressive \" ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"either transmitting more easily","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"or replicating faster inside the body .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"However , this theory is speculative at this stage","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"- there haven ' t yet been direct comparisons","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"to see","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"whether people","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"who catch one version of the virus","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"are more likely to pass it on or suffer more severe symptoms .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"Many individuals","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"who get coronavirus","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"will experience nothing worse than seasonal flu symptoms ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"but the overall profile of the disease ,","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"including its mortality rate ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"looks more serious .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"At the start of an outbreak the apparent mortality rate can be an overestimate","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"if a lot of mild cases are being missed .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"But Bruce Aylward , a WHO expert ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"who led an international mission to China","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"to learn about the virus and the country ' s response ,","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"this has not been the case with Covid-19 .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"The evidence did not suggest","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"that we were only seeing the tip of the iceberg .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"If borne out by further testing ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"this could mean","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"that current estimates of a roughly 1 % fatality rate are accurate .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"This would make Covid-19 about 10 times more deadly than seasonal flu ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"which is estimated to kill between 290,000 and 650,000 people a year globally .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"Claim :","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"' It only kills the elderly ,","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"so younger people can relax '","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"Most people","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"who are not elderly","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"and do not have underlying health conditions","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"will not become critically ill from Covid-19 .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"But the illness still has a higher chance","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"of leading to serious respiratory symptoms","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"than seasonal flu","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"and there are other at-risk groups -","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"health workers , for instance , are more vulnerable","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"because they are likely to have higher exposure to the virus .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"The actions","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"that young , healthy people take ,","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"including reporting symptoms and following quarantine instructions ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"will have an important role","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"in protecting the most vulnerable in society","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"and in shaping the overall trajectory of the outbreak .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Claim :","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"' You need to be with an infected person for 10 minutes '","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"For flu , some hospital guidelines define exposure as being within six feet of an infected person","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"who sneezes or coughs for 10 minutes or longer .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"However , it is possible to be infected with shorter interactions or even by picking the virus up from contaminated surfaces ,","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"although this is thought to be a less common route of transmission .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Claim :","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"' A vaccine could be ready within a few months '","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"Scientists were quick out of the gates","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"in beginning development of a vaccine for the new coronavirus ,","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"helped by the early release of the genetic sequence by Chinese researchers .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"The development of a viable vaccine continues apace ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"with several teams now testing candidates in animal experiments .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"However , the incremental trials","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"required","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"before a commercial vaccine could be rolled out","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"are still a lengthy undertaking","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"- and an essential one","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"to ensure","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"that even rare side-effects are spotted .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"A commercially available vaccine within a year would be quick . '","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":247,"left":127,"right":246,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":0,"right":126,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":126,"left":1,"right":125,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":152,"right":245,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":133,"right":151,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":133,"left":128,"right":132,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":6,"right":131,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":7,"right":130,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":130,"left":129,"right":10,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":136,"right":150,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":134,"right":135,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":141,"right":149,"relation":"explanation","nuclearit